Description of incident: The names and SSNs of 4,624              Floridians were accessible on the Internet for approximately 18 days              in September. The data were not accessible through websites, but              an individual came across the information when Googling his own name.              The agency has asked Google to remove the pages from its cache, and              has notified all affected individuals by mail.  Individuals who had registered with Florida 's Agency for Workforce Innovation were affected.
